<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>The Fox Who Chased the Moon</title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Lora:ital@0;1&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    :root {
      --ink: #1a0f00;
      --paper: #f5ede0;
      --amber: #c96a1a;
      --rust: #8b3a0f;
      --dusk: #2b1e3a;
      --moon: #f7e7c1;
      --mist: #e8d9c5;
    }

    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

    body {
      background: var(--paper);
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
      overflow-x: hidden;
      cursor: default;
    }

    /* ── Sky header ── */
    .sky {
      position: relative;
      min-height: 100vh;
      background: linear-gradient(175deg, var(--dusk) 0%, #4a2c5a 40%, #a0522d 75%, var(--amber) 100%);
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    /* Stars */
    .stars {
      position: absolute; inset: 0;
      pointer-events: none;
    }
    .star {
      position: absolute;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: #fff;
      animation: twinkle var(--d, 3s) ease-in-out infinite;
      opacity: 0;
    }
    @keyframes twinkle {
      0%, 100% { opacity: 0; transform: scale(0.8); }
      50%       { opacity: var(--o, 0.8); transform: scale(1.2); }
    }

    /* Moon */
    .moon {
      position: absolute;
      top: 10%;
      right: 18%;
      width: 90px; height: 90px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--moon);
      box-shadow: 0 0 40px 10px rgba(247,231,193,0.4), 0 0 80px 20px rgba(247,231,193,0.15);
      animation: moonGlow 4s ease-in-out infinite;
    }
    @keyframes moonGlow {
      0%, 100% { box-shadow: 0 0 40px 10px rgba(247,231,193,0.4), 0 0 80px 20px rgba(247,231,193,0.15); }
      50%       { box-shadow: 0 0 60px 20px rgba(247,231,193,0.6), 0 0 120px 40px rgba(247,231,193,0.25); }
    }

    /* Fox SVG illustration */
    .fox-wrap {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 0; left: 50%;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      width: 260px;
      animation: foxBob 3s ease-in-out infinite;
    }
    @keyframes foxBob {
      0%, 100% { transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(0); }
      50%       { transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(-8px); }
    }

    /* Ground silhouette */
    .ground {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 120px;
      background: #0d0705;
      clip-path: ellipse(60% 100% at 50% 100%);
    }
    .trees {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 180px;
      display: flex; align-items: flex-end;
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    /* Title text */
    .hero-text {
      position: relative; z-index: 2;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 200px;
      animation: fadeUp 1.2s ease both;
    }
    @keyframes fadeUp {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(30px); }
      to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }
    .hero-text h1 {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
      color: var(--moon);
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: -0.5px;
      text-shadow: 0 2px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    }
    .hero-text h1 em {
      color: var(--amber);
      font-style: italic;
    }
    .hero-text .byline {
      margin-top: 14px;
      color: rgba(247,231,193,0.55);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      letter-spacing: 3px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    /* ── Story sections ── */
    .story {
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 80px 30px 100px;
    }

    .chapter {
      margin-bottom: 80px;
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(40px);
      transition: opacity 0.8s ease, transform 0.8s ease;
    }
    .chapter.visible {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: none;
    }

    .chapter-num {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 4px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--amber);
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .chapter h2 {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.5vw, 2.4rem);
      line-height: 1.2;
      color: var(--rust);
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .chapter p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: #3a2010;
    }
    .chapter p + p { margin-top: 16px; }

    .chapter p em {
      color: var(--rust);
      font-style: italic;
    }

    /* Decorative divider */
    .divider {
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px;
      margin: 50px 0;
      opacity: 0.35;
    }
    .divider span { flex: 1; height: 1px; background: var(--rust); }
    .divider::before { content: "✦"; color: var(--amber); font-size: 1rem; }

    /* Pull quote */
    .pull {
      border-left: 3px solid var(--amber);
      padding: 12px 24px;
      margin: 28px 0;
      background: rgba(201,106,26,0.06);
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    }
    .pull p {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 1.15rem !important;
      color: var(--rust) !important;
    }

    /* Inline fox paw emoji accent */
    .accent {
      display: inline-block;
      font-size: 1.3em;
      margin-right: 6px;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }

    /* Footer */
    footer {
      background: var(--dusk);
      color: rgba(247,231,193,0.4);
      text-align: center;
      padding: 40px 20px;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    footer span { color: var(--amber); }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ── Hero ── -->
<section class="sky">

  <!-- Starfield -->
  <div class="stars" id="stars"></div>

  <!-- Moon -->
  <div class="moon"></div>

  <!-- Title -->
  <div class="hero-text">
    <h1>The Fox Who<br/>Chased the <em>Moon</em></h1>
    <p class="byline">A small story for quiet evenings</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Ground -->
  <div class="ground"></div>

  <!-- Fox SVG -->
  <div class="fox-wrap">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 260 200" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <!-- Tail -->
      <path d="M60 160 Q20 140 10 100 Q5 70 30 80 Q50 90 65 120 Z" fill="#c96a1a"/>
      <path d="M30 80 Q5 70 10 100 Q5 80 25 90 Z" fill="#f5ede0"/>
      <!-- Body -->
      <ellipse cx="120" cy="155" rx="60" ry="35" fill="#c96a1a"/>
      <!-- Head -->
      <ellipse cx="170" cy="115" rx="38" ry="32" fill="#c96a1a"/>
      <!-- Ears -->
      <polygon points="148,90 140,55 165,82" fill="#c96a1a"/>
      <polygon points="148,90 145,65 162,84" fill="#8b3a0f"/>
      <polygon points="188,88 195,52 175,80" fill="#c96a1a"/>
      <polygon points="187,88 192,63 177,82" fill="#8b3a0f"/>
      <!-- Face white -->
      <ellipse cx="176" cy="125" rx="22" ry="18" fill="#f5ede0"/>
      <!-- Eyes -->
      <circle cx="162" cy="110" r="5" fill="#1a0f00"/>
      <circle cx="182" cy="110" r="5" fill="#1a0f00"/>
      <circle cx="164" cy="108" r="1.5" fill="white"/>
      <circle cx="184" cy="108" r="1.5" fill="white"/>
      <!-- Nose -->
      <ellipse cx="172" cy="122" rx="4" ry="3" fill="#8b3a0f"/>
      <!-- Mouth -->
      <path d="M168 125 Q172 130 176 125" stroke="#8b3a0f" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
      <!-- Legs -->
      <rect x="95"  y="180" width="16" height="18" rx="5" fill="#c96a1a"/>
      <rect x="118" y="180" width="16" height="18" rx="5" fill="#c96a1a"/>
      <rect x="141" y="180" width="16" height="18" rx="5" fill="#c96a1a"/>
      <rect x="164" y="180" width="16" height="18" rx="5" fill="#c96a1a"/>
    </svg>
  </div>

</section>

<!-- ── Story ── -->
<main class="story">

  <div class="chapter" data-chapter>
    <p class="chapter-num">Chapter I</p>
    <h2>The Fox at the Edge of the Wood</h2>
    <p>
      There was once a small fox named <em>Ember</em>, who lived at the edge of a
      great pine forest where the trees smelled of resin and cold rain. She had
      bright copper fur, a white-tipped tail, and an unbearable habit of
      wanting things she could not have.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every night, she would sit on the mossy stone at the clearing's border and
      stare up at the moon — round and silver, impossibly calm — and feel a
      pull in her chest like a fishhook catching on a rib.
    </p>
    <div class="pull">
      <p>"If I ran fast enough," she thought, "I could reach the hill where the
      moon rests. I've seen it touch the treetops. I've seen it balance on the
      mountain's shoulder. It cannot be that far."</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"><span></span></div>

  <div class="chapter" data-chapter>
    <p class="chapter-num">Chapter II</p>
    <h2>The Long Chase</h2>
    <p>
      One autumn night, when the moon hung especially low and golden, Ember
      decided to run. She leapt from the stone and sprinted across the meadow,
      paws barely brushing the frost-tipped grass, tail streaming behind her
      like a flame.
    </p>
    <p>
      She ran past the old mill pond, past the three birches that grew twisted
      together like friends whispering a secret, past the ridge of broken
      stones where the rabbits slept. The moon sat always just ahead —
      <em>close, so close</em> — perched on the next hill's crest.
    </p>
    <p>
      She climbed that hill. The moon moved to the next. She climbed that one
      too. And the next. Her breath came in silver puffs. Her paws ached. But
      the moon was never where she arrived — only ever where she was going.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"><span></span></div>

  <div class="chapter" data-chapter>
    <p class="chapter-num">Chapter III</p>
    <h2>What the River Told Her</h2>
    <p>
      Just before dawn, exhausted, Ember stopped beside a river she had never
      seen before. She bent to drink — and there was the moon again, trembling
      in the dark water below her nose.
    </p>
    <p>
      She did not try to catch it. She was too tired for that. She only looked.
    </p>
    <div class="pull">
      <p>The moon in the river looked back at her with the same patient,
      indifferent light it always had. And for the first time, Ember noticed
      that it was beautiful precisely because it could not be held.</p>
    </div>
    <p>
      She curled up on the riverbank, tucked her nose under her tail, and slept
      while the moon moved slowly overhead, keeping its own company, going
      wherever moons go.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"><span></span></div>

  <div class="chapter" data-chapter>
    <p class="chapter-num">Epilogue</p>
    <h2>Every Night, Still</h2>
    <p>
      Ember found her way home as the sun rose. She never chased the moon again.
      But every evening she would return to her mossy stone, sit very still, and
      watch it climb the sky — <em>and that was enough.</em>
    </p>
    <p>
      Some things are not meant to be caught. They are meant to be followed at
      a comfortable distance, with wonder, for as long as the night allows.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top: 30px; font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-style: italic; color: var(--amber); text-align: center; font-size: 1.1rem;">
      — The End —
    </p>
  </div>

</main>

<footer>
  A story about <span>wanting</span>, <span>chasing</span>, and finally <span>resting</span>.
</footer>

<script>
  // Generate stars
  const container = document.getElementById('stars');
  for (let i = 0; i < 120; i++) {
    const s = document.createElement('div');
    s.className = 'star';
    const size = Math.random() * 2.5 + 0.5;
    s.style.cssText = `
      width: ${size}px; height: ${size}px;
      top: ${Math.random() * 75}%;
      left: ${Math.random() * 100}%;
      --d: ${(Math.random() * 4 + 2).toFixed(1)}s;
      --o: ${(Math.random() * 0.6 + 0.3).toFixed(2)};
      animation-delay: ${(Math.random() * 5).toFixed(1)}s;
    `;
    container.appendChild(s);
  }

  // Scroll reveal
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(e => {
      if (e.isIntersecting) {
        e.target.classList.add('visible');
        observer.unobserve(e.target);
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.15 });

  document.querySelectorAll('[data-chapter]').forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
</script>
</body>
</html>
